BBT BAMAGAS INTRASTATE, LLC Statement of Operating Conditions for Transportation Service Record: 20-Section 19 (Park and Loan Service) Issued: April 1, 2017 Version: (1.0.0) Effective: September 27, 2022 19. APPLICABILITY AND CHARACTER OF PARK AND LOAN SERVICE. 19.1 Applicability. This Statement shall also apply to all Park and Loan Service rendered by Transporter for Shipper pursuant to Part 284 of the FERC's regulations and the Transportation Agreement for service under this Statement. 19.2 General. Service under this provision shall be provided up to Shipper's MDQ in Shipper's Park and Loan Service Agreement to the extent Transporter's System permits the provision of such service and that the provision of such service shall not prevent Transporter from meeting all of its Firm Service and Interruptible Service obligations, including Transporter's System's needs. 19.3 Parking Service. (a) Subject to the terms and provisions of a Park and Loan Service Agreement, Shipper agrees to deliver or cause Gas to be delivered to Transporter and Transporter agrees to: (i) Receive a quantity of Gas ("Parked Quantity"), up to the MDQ specified in the Park and Loan Service Agreement, on behalf of Shipper at the applicable Transaction Point on Transporter's System; (ii) Hold the Parked Quantity on Transporter's System for a minimum of one (1) Day; and (iii) Deliver, upon nomination by Shipper, the Parked Quantity to Shipper at the same Transaction Point. (b) Shipper shall receive or deliver Gas from or to Transporter at the Transaction Point by delivering the scheduled quantities to or from an Interruptible Service Agreement to be entered into by and between Shipper and Transporter. Shipper shall make any necessary arrangements with Transporter or third parties to receive or deliver Gas to Transporter at the Transaction Point; provided, however, that such arrangements shall be compatible with the operating conditions of Transporter's System and shall provide for coordinated scheduling with Transporter. (c) In the event Transporter does not have sufficient capacity on a given Day to satisfy all nominations to park or withdraw Gas, Transporter shall schedule nominations in sequence, starting with the nomination of the Shipper paying the highest rate for parking service. If two (2) or more Shippers are paying the same rate for parking service and Transporter lacks sufficient capacity to schedule such Shippers' nominations, such nominations shall be scheduled on a pro-rata basis, using the quantities that would otherwise be scheduled. (d) To protect or maintain the operational integrity of Transporter's System, Transporter may require the withdrawal of quantities of Gas in Shipper's PAL Account as soon as practical after Transporter's notice to Shipper, not to exceed three (3) Days of notice. In the event Shipper does not cause the withdrawal of specified quantities of Gas within three (3) Day period after notice, Transporter shall have the right to purchase all or any portion of the remaining quantities of Gas in Shipper's PAL Account and Shipper shall convey title to such Gas free and clear of any adverse claims at a price equal to fifty percent (50%) of the Cash-Out Price. (e) Parking service shall be subject to curtailment or interruption without liability pursuant to Section 12 and Section 19.7 hereof. 19.4 Lending Service. (a) Subject to the terms and provisions of a lending service agreement, Transporter agrees to deliver or cause Gas to be delivered to Shipper and Shipper agrees to: (i) Receive a quantity of Gas ("Loaned Quantity"), equal to the MDQ specified in the Park and Loan Service Agreement, on behalf of Shipper at the applicable Transaction Point on Transporter's System; and, (ii) At the time such advances are scheduled, agree to a redelivery schedule for the Loaned Quantity setting out the dates and daily quantities of Gas Shipper will redeliver to Transporter at, unless otherwise mutually agreed to, the Transaction Point until the Loaned Quantity equals zero (0). (b) Shipper shall receive or deliver Gas from or to Transporter at the Transaction Point by delivering the scheduled quantities to or from an Interruptible Service Agreement to be entered into by and between Shipper and Transporter. Shipper shall make any necessary arrangements with Transporter or third parties to receive or deliver Gas to Transporter at the Transaction Point; provided, however, that such arrangements shall be compatible with the operating conditions of Transporter's System and shall provide for coordinated scheduling with Transporter. (c) In the event Transporter does not have sufficient capacity on a given Day to satisfy all nominations to borrow or repay Gas, Transporter shall schedule nominations in sequence, starting with the nomination of the Shipper paying the highest rate for lending service. If two or more Shippers are paying the same rate for lending service and Transporter lacks sufficient capacity to schedule all Shippers' nominations paying that rate, the nominations of such Shippers shall be scheduled on a pro-rata basis, using the quantities that would otherwise be scheduled. (d) To protect or maintain the operational integrity of Transporter's System, Transporter may require Shipper to adjust its redelivery schedule and redeliver quantities of Gas in Shipper's lending account from time to time. (e) Lending service shall be subject to curtailment or interruption without liability to Transporter pursuant to Section 12 and Section 19.7 hereof. (f) If Transporter, upon nomination by Shipper, fails to schedule quantities of Gas for return to Transporter within the planned redelivery schedule, Transporter and Shipper will agree to a revised redelivery schedule. Additionally, Transporter shall suspend the lending rate charges for the quantity of Gas nominated but not scheduled for as long as the interruption or curtailment is in effect. 19.5 Separate Accounts. Transporter shall maintain separate parking service and lending service accounts ("PAL Account") for each Shipper utilizing the Park and Loan Services hereunder. Transporter shall receive from or advance to Shipper such daily quantities of Gas nominated and scheduled for receipt or delivery by Transporter, and park or lend such gas for a minimum of one (1) Day. Such quantities received or advanced shall be recorded in Shipper's PAL Account, as applicable. Shippers electing to withdraw parked gas or redeliver loaned gas from their respective PAL Account shall nominate a quantity up to the quantity of gas available in their respective PAL Account at the point the gas was either received or advanced by Transporter. 19.6 Separate Transportation Agreements. If Transporter and Shipper agree that Shipper may receive parked gas quantities or return loaned gas quantities at points that are different from those specified in the Park and Loan Service Agreement, Shipper and Transporter must utilize a separate Interruptible Service Agreement to effectuate receipt or delivery of such Gas at the new points. 19.7 Withdrawal upon Termination. Not more than thirty (30) days after the termination of Shipper's Park and Loan Service Agreement, Transporter will notify Shipper of Shipper's PAL Account balance. Shipper will nominate to eliminate any remaining balance within thirty (30) days of the date of Transporter's notice. 19.8 Other Conditions of Service. (a) Service rendered hereunder shall be Interruptible Service. (b) Transporter and Shipper shall execute a new transaction confirmation for each Park and Loan Service agreed to hereunder. Each transaction confirmation shall set forth a deal number for each transaction which Shipper shall use when nominating its Park and Loan Service hereunder. 19.9 Subject to Laws. Transporter's Park and Loan Service is subject to all present and future valid laws and lawful rules, regulations, and orders of all regulatory authorities now or hereafter having jurisdiction over the services or facilities used to provide such services. The Parties acknowledge that Park and Loan Service under this Statement is subject to the provisions of the Subpart G Regulations. Shipper warrants that at all times during the term of the Transportation Agreement, Shipper will commit no action or omission that will cause the Park and Loan Service provided to Shipper to fail to comply with all applicable rules and regulations of the applicable regulatory agencies, including, without limitation, the "on behalf of" provisions of the Part 284 regulations. 19.10 Required Information. Upon request, Shipper must furnish to Transporter all information that is required for Transporter to comply with any reporting requirements of the FERC or any other duly constituted authorities.
End of Statement
